    "abstract": "GENERator is a generative genomic foundation model for long-context DNA modeling (context up to 98k nucleotides), pre-trained on 386 billion nucleotides of eukaryotic DNA from RefSeq. It uses a LLaMA decoder-only architecture with 6-mer tokenization and an autoregressive next-token objective. It matches or exceeds SOTA on sequence recovery, zero-shot variant effect prediction, and fine-tuned genomic benchmarks, and enables prompt-guided cis-regulatory element design.",
    "domain": "Multimodal",
